  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Abnormal uterine bleeding encompasses abnormalities in the regularity, duration of flow,
      frequency, and/or blood flow volume relative to normal menstruation. Of these menstrual
      abnormalities, heavy menstrual bleeding (HMB), defined objectively as a blood loss of 80 ml
      or more per menstrual cycle , which is unrelated to pregnancy or known pelvic or systemic
      disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
